The paper deals with the problem of finding a small universal point set for a class of graphs, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG). The size of the point set is related to the structure of the graphs, which suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the study of graph algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The problem of finding small universal point sets is closely related to the study of graph drawing and visualization (cs.GT), and the paper provides a new result in this area. The authors use techniques from discrete mathematics (cs.DM) to analyze the structure of 2-outerplanar graphs and construct a small universal point set for them. Finally, the paper may also be relevant to the study of computational geometry and topology (cs.SI) due to its focus on planar embeddings of graphs.
